<subSubSection pageId="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,926,2001]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,926,951]" pageId="6">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The only Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1917" box="[647,773,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Monohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[647,773,926,950]" italics="true" pageId="6">Monohelea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which the males have hind femur with brown base, mid leg with distinct mesal brown bands, paramere with mesal hook-shaped process measuring 0.61X as long as distal portion that progressively narrows distally to rounded apex. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,926,2001]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1037,1062]" pageId="6">Male.</emphasis>
Head: eyes widely separated (
<figureCitation box="[621,721,1037,1062]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 4 C</figureCitation>
). Antenna missing. Palpus (
<figureCitation box="[1044,1143,1037,1062]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 4 D</figureCitation>
) pale brown; 3rd segment nearly oval with small, shallow, sensory organ on apical 1/3; lengths of segments 20- 25- 25- 25- 43; palpal ratio 1.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,926,2001]" pageId="6">
Thorax. Brown; scutum damaged. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[664,757,1145,1170]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 4 F</figureCitation>
) yellow; fore leg missing, mid-, hind coxae and trochanters brown; mid femur with basal and mesal pale brown bands, hind femur with basal brown band, one brown stripe in middle, a subapical ventral brown spot; mid tibiae with a mesal and apical pale brown band; hind tibia missing. Tarsi: mid tarsomere 1 with 2 basal, 2 apical spines; mid tarsomeres 2–4 with 2-2-2 apical spines, basal spines absent; mid tarsomere 5 missing; mid tarsal ratio 2.22; claws missing. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1199,1289,1314]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 4 A</figureCitation>
) partially damaged; macrotrichia restricted to vein costa; microtrichia absent; 2nd radial cell nearly 
<date box="[1070,1105,1328,1352]" pageId="6">2X</date>
longer than 1st; wing length nearly 
<quantity box="[229,332,1365,1389]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.90 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[417,521,1365,1389]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="6" unit="mm" value="0.34">0.34 mm</quantity>
; costal ratio nearly 0.75. Halter stem pale; knob pale brown in distal 1/2, a pale brown spot laterally (
<figureCitation box="[390,477,1400,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig 4 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,926,2001]" pageId="6">
Abdomen. Pale brown (
<figureCitation box="[470,567,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 4 E</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[708,818,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1327,1349]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,211,1287]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov., male. A. Wing; B. Thorax showing halter; C. Head, anterior view; D.Palpus, lateral view; E. Abdomen, ventral view; F. Legs (up to botton) hind femur, mid leg, lateral view; G.Genitalia, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067524/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Figs. 4 G</figureCitation>
; 9 E–F): sternite IX spiculate except on basal portion, posterior margin with a short, convex, median lobe with 4 long setae; tergite IX tapering with a pair of apicolateral processes. Gonocoxite moderately stout, nearly 1.8 X longer than basal width; gonostylus curved in apical 1/2, 0.59 as long as gonocoxite, moderately pilose on basal 3/4. Parameres (
<figureCitation box="[912,1006,1544,1569]" captionStart="FIGURE9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[278,1266,201,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[207,1344,189,1889]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE9. Parameres and aedeagus. A–B.Monohelea barbara Felippe-Bauer&amp; Trindade sp. nov.; C–D.Monohelea cornuta Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; E–F. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; G–H. Monohelea forceps Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067534/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 9 E</figureCitation>
) 1.36 X as long as aedeagus, broadly fused at trilobed base; each with a long, curved, sclerotized mesal hook-shaped process, 0.61X as long as distal portion of the paramere, that tapering gradually to blunt apex. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1118,1616,1641]" captionStart="FIGURE9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[278,1266,201,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[207,1344,189,1889]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE9. Parameres and aedeagus. A–B.Monohelea barbara Felippe-Bauer&amp; Trindade sp. nov.; C–D.Monohelea cornuta Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; E–F. Monohelea ema Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov.; G–H. Monohelea forceps Felippe-Bauer &amp; Trindade sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1067534/files/figure.png" pageId="6">Fig. 9 F</figureCitation>
) triangular, composed of 2 pointed ventral plates, with slightly sclerotized dorsal structure, which arises in the middle way to aedeagus base, and produced beyond the apices of ventral plates, ending as an apical projection; basal arms slender, slightly expanded laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,926,2001]" box="[199,410,1760,1785]" pageId="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1760,1785]" pageId="6">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
